800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F01%2Fpune-couple-3-1738041533.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D489112%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anirudha%20and%20Sucheta%20Ambekar%2C%20both%20IT%20professionals%2C%20turned%20their%20longing%20for%20rural%20life%20into%20reality.%20Their%20sustainable%20home%2C%20%E2%80%98Anant%20Farms%E2%80%99%2C%20near%20Pune%2C%20is%20built%20using%20stones%20and%20antique%20teakwood%2C%20emulating%20traditional%20architecture%20while%20incorporating%20modern%20sustainability%20practices%2C%20including%20rainwater%20harvesting%20and%20solar%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F489112%2Fpune-couple-build-sustainable-eco-friendly-home-practice-organic-farming-harvest-rainwater-solar-energy-2%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20The%20Man%20Who%20Swapped%20the%20Gun%20for%20a%20Camera%20%26amp%3B%20Gave%20Us%20India%E2%80%99s%20First%20Tiger%20Photo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFrederick%20Walter%20Champion%2C%20an%20ex-soldier%20in%20the%20British%20Indian%20Army%2C%20an%20officer%20of%20the%20Imperial%20Forestry%20Service%20%5B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2Ftags%2Findian-forest-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndian%20Forest%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%5D%20and%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%2C%20took%20the%20first%20photograph%20of%20a%20tiger%20in%20the%20wild%20in%20India.%20A%201921-batch%20officer%2C%20Champion%20served%20in%20the%20United%20Provinces%20(corresponding%20to%20approximately%20present-day%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Uttarakhand)%20until%201947%20and%20rose%20to%20the%20rank%20of%20deputy%20conservator%20of%20forests.%20A%20pioneer%20of%20the%20camera%20trapping%20technique%2C%20he%20was%20also%20credited%20as%20a%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20photography%20in%20India%20by%20Jim%20Corbett.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20Corbett%2C%20Champion%E2%80%99s%20undying%20commitment%20to%20conservation%20inspired%20him%20to%20give%20up%20the%20gun%20for%20the%20camera%2C%20and%20together%2C%20they%20became%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20national%20park%20established%20in%201935%2C%20which%20was%20renamed%20Corbett%20National%20Park%20in%201957.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%2024%20August%201893%20in%20Surrey%2C%20England%2C%20Champion%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20family%20of%20nature%20lovers%20with%20his%20father%20George%20Charles%20Champion%2C%20an%20entomologist.%20His%20brother%2C%20Sir%20Harry%20George%20Champion%2C%20a%20forester%2C%20was%20credited%20later%20on%20with%20creating%20a%20classification%20of%20the%20forest%20types%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampion%20first%20came%20to%20India%20in%20the%20early%201910s%2C%20serving%20in%20the%20East%20Bengal%20police%20department%20until%201916%2C%20following%20which%20he%20was%20commissioned%20into%20the%20British%20Indian%20Army%20Reserve%20of%20Officers%20(Cavalry%20branch).%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F165293%2Fww1-india-soldiers-punjab-memorial-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAfter%20World%20War%20I%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20his%20retirement%20from%20the%20army%20in%20the%20early%201920s%2C%20he%20joined%20the%20Imperial%20Forestry%20Service.%20Unlike%20other%20officers%20of%20his%20era%2C%20he%20detested%20the%20idea%20of%20shooting%20animals%20for%20sport%20and%20preferred%20documenting%20them%20through%20wildlife%20photography.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-288515%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201072px)%20100vw%2C%201072px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239.png%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221072%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FW%20Champion's%20photo%20of%20tiger%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239.png%201072w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239-300x215.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239-500x358.png%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239-768x549.png%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2FFW-Champion-Tiger-3-1655376239-150x107.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-288515%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22767%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E(Image%20courtesy%20Twitter%2FRaza%20Kazmi)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETripwire%20photography%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20joining%20the%20IFS%2C%20Champion%20had%20tried%20to%20obtain%20an%20image%20of%20a%20tiger%20in%20its%20natural%20habitat.%20As%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20noted%20in%20a%20Twitter%20thread%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20took%20him%208%20long%20years%20to%20finally%20get%20these%20images.%E2%80%9D%20Taken%20in%20the%20Kumaon%20forests%2C%20these%20images%20were%20first%20published%20on%20the%20front%20page%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Illustrated%20London%20News%E2%80%99%20on%203%20October%201925%20with%20the%20accompanying%20headline%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20Triumph%20of%20Big%20Game%20Photography%3A%20The%20First%20Photographs%20of%20Tigers%20in%20the%20Natural%20Haunts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20he%20came%20out%20with%20a%20book%20titled%2C%20%E2%80%98With%20Camera%20in%20Tiger-Land%E2%80%99.%20This%20book%20set%20new%20precedents%20for%20publishing%20%E2%80%9Cphotographs%20of%20wild%20animals%2C%20just%20as%20they%20live%20their%20everyday%20lives%20in%20the%20great%20Indian%20jungles%2C%20away%20from%20the%20every-destroying%20hand%20of%20man%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20ones%20marked%20by%20these%20majestic%20animals%20running%20from%20beaters%2C%20about%20to%20be%20and%20eventually%20shot%20by%20hunters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pain-staking%20technique%20he%20employed%20to%20shoot%20these%20photographs%20was%20called%20%E2%80%98trip-wire%20photography%E2%80%99.%20As%20Raza%20Kazmi%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20tiger%20(or%20any%20other%20animal)%20tripped%20on%20a%20wire%20carefully%20concealed%20below%20his%20usual%20walking%20path%20resulting%20in%20him%20taking%20his%20own%20image%2C%20usually%20by%20the%20night%20as%20the%20flashes%20connected%20to%20the%20wire%20went%20off%20simultaneously.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampion%20described%20this%20process%20in%20a%20letter%20accompanying%20the%20piece%20in%20%E2%80%98The%20Illustrated%20London%20News%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20photographs%20are%20quite%20unique%2C%20no%20satisfactory%20photographs%20ever%20having%20been%20taken%20before%2C%20to%20my%20knowledge%2C%20of%20tigers%20in%20their%20native%20haunts.%E2%80%9D%20Going%20further%2C%20he%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20flash%20is%20so%20sudden%20that%20he%20probably%20takes%20it%20for%20a%20flash%20of%20lightning.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20implications%20of%20this%20technique%20have%20been%20far%20and%20wide.%20Further%20refined%20in%20the%20subsequent%20decades%2C%20this%20technique%20is%20today%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98camera%20trap%20photography%E2%80%99.%20Conservationists%20today%20use%20this%20method%20to%20calculate%20tiger%20census%20and%20monitor%20their%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Mahesh%20Rangarajan%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20history%20and%20environmental%20studies%20at%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20states%20in%20this%20column%20for%20The%20Telegraph%2C%20%E2%80%9COf%20the%20200%20camera%20traps%20placed%20by%20Champion%2C%20tigers%20came%20by%20on%20only%2018%20occasions.%20In%20all%2C%20he%20had%2011%20shots%20of%20nine%20individuals%2C%20but%20this%20was%20enough%20to%20prove%20how%20each%20animal%20had%20distinct%20stripe%20patterns.%20This%20was%20a%20path-breaker%20in%20every%20sense.%20Over%20the%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20scientists%20the%20world%20over%20working%20with%20far%20more%20advanced%20cameras%20and%20aided%20by%20software%20can%20tell%20a%20tiger%20by%20his%20or%20her%20stripes.%20It%20is%20now%20a%20widely%20used%20technique%20worldwide%2C%20and%20its%20pioneer%20was%20a%20deputy%20conservator%20of%20forests%20nearly%20a%20hundred%20years%20ago.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20give%20us%20some%20context%20on%20how%20difficult%20this%20process%20was%20for%20Champion%2C%20K%20Ullas%20Karanth%2C%20a%20leading%20tiger%20expert%20based%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20wrote%20this%20in%20his%20introduction%20to%20%E2%80%98Tripwire%20for%20a%20Tiger%2C%20Selected%20works%20of%20FW%20Champion%E2%80%99%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20I%20struggled%20with%20my%20camera%20traps%2C%20trying%20to%20photograph%20tigers%20to%20get%20a%20more%20accurate%20count%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20using%2035mm%20SLR%20cameras%20and%20tripwires%2C%20I%20marvelled%20at%20Champion%E2%80%99s%20tenacity%20with%20his%20archaic%20camera%20traps%2C%2060%20years%20earlier.%20I%20was%20astounded%20to%20learn%20from%20his%20accounts%20that%2C%20after%2030%20years%20of%20using%20camera%20traps%20in%20prime%20tiger%20jungles%2C%20Fred%20Champion%20managed%20to%20get%20just%20nine%20high-quality%20photos%20of%20tigers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20photographer%20friends%2C%20Champion%20even%20gave%20what%20we%20today%20call%20the%20EXIF%20details%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6although%20the%20photograph%20of%20the%20tiger%20pulling%20his%20kill%20was%20taken%20at%201-50%20sec.%20on%20a%20special%20rapid%20plate%3B%20suitable%20exposures%20are%20from%201-150%20to%201-200%20sec.%2C%20with%20f6.8%20on%20an%20ultra-rapid%20plate%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fq4Ro1PCSn5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fq4Ro1PCSn5%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Raza%20Kazmi%20(%40RazaKazmi17)%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRazaKazmi17%2Fstatus%2F1534373335609790470%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%20June%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELegacy%20as%20conservationist%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20his%20role%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Father%20of%20Camera%20Trap%20Photography%E2%80%99%2C%20Champion%20also%20played%20a%20pivotal%20part%20in%20leading%20the%20conversation%20around%20wildlife%20conservation%20at%20a%20time%20when%20British%20officials%20took%20pride%20in%20big%20game%20hunting.%20Concerned%20about%20the%20dwindling%20number%20of%20tigers%20due%20to%20hunting%2C%20he%20allotted%20%E2%80%9Cshooting%20blocks%20where%20there%20were%20likely%20to%20be%20no%20tigers%20for%20hunters%20to%20shoot%2C%E2%80%9D%20wrote%20Rangarajan.%20Also%2C%20he%20strongly%20advocated%20for%20limiting%20gun%20licences%2C%20preventing%20motorcars%20from%20entering%20reserved%20forests%20and%20reducing%20cash%20rewards%20for%20killing%20wildlife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Shivaliks%2C%20where%20Champion%20had%20served%20with%20real%20distinction%2C%20contained%20shooting%20blocks%20of%20the%20governor-general.%20Before%20Corbet%20came%20across%20Champion%E2%80%99s%20works%20including%20%E2%80%98With%20a%20Camera%20in%20Tiger-Land%E2%80%99%20(1927)%20and%20%E2%80%98Jungle%20in%20Sunlight%20and%20Shadow%E2%80%99%20(1934)%2C%20he%20would%20organise%20big%20game%20shoots%20for%20top%20officials%20of%20the%20British%20Indian%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20India%20attained%20Independence%2C%20however%2C%20C%20Rajagopalachari%20(Rajaji)%2C%20a%20freedom%20fighter%20and%20the%20second%20and%20last%20governor-general%20of%20India%2C%20changed%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20said%20that%20when%20Rajaji%2C%20the%20newly%20appointed%20Governor%20General%2C%20was%20invited%20for%20a%20hunt%20but%20he%20was%20so%20impressed%20by%20the%20biological%20diversity%20and%20plethora%20of%20wild%20animals%20in%20the%20area%20that%20instead%20of%20hunting%2C%20he%20suggested%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20wildlife%20sanctuary%20in%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20this%20description%20on%20the%20Rajaji%20Tiger%20Reserve%20website.%20Thus%2C%20out%20of%20the%20shooting%20blocks%20in%20the%20Shivaliks%2C%20a%20sanctuary%20was%20carved%20out%20in%201948%20and%20today%20it%E2%80%99s%20known%20as%20the%20Rajaji%20National%20Park%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cextends%20over%20the%20Shivalik%20Range%20from%20the%20Dehradun-Saharanpur%20road%20in%20the%20north-west%20to%20the%20Rawasan%20River%20in%20the%20southeast%2C%20with%20the%20Ganges%20dividing%20it%20into%20two%20parts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%201947%2C%20Champion%20left%20for%20East%20Africa%2C%20where%20he%20said%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20British%20tea%20planter%20and%20naturalist%20Edward%20Pritchard%20Gee%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnimal%20photography%20here%20is%20too%20easy%E2%80%9D.%20He%20was%20nostalgic%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20my%20friends%2C%20the%20tigers%20of%20India%2C%20which%20can%20at%20no%20time%20be%20photographed%20easily.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20him%20from%20adding%20valuable%20inputs%20to%20the%20global%20discourse%20on%20wildlife%20conservation.%20Noting%20that%20%E2%80%9Cevery%20creature%20has%20its%20place%20in%20nature%E2%80%99s%20balanced%20scheme%20of%20wildlife%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20argued%20that%20predators%20like%20the%20leopard%2C%20wild%20dog%20or%20jackals%20weren%E2%80%99t%20bloodthirsty%20animals%20who%20deserved%20to%20be%20shot%20down%20and%20that%20the%20best%20course%20of%20action%20would%20be%20to%20leave%20them%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20other%20animals%2C%20his%20book%20%E2%80%98The%20Jungle%20in%20Sunlight%20and%20Shadow%E2%80%99%20explores%20the%20forests%20he%20witnessed%20in%20India%20beyond%20the%20tiger-like%20the%20scaly%20ant-eater%2C%20honey%20badger%2C%20swamp%20deer%20and%20the%20pangolin%2C%20amongst%20others.%20He%20would%20also%20go%20on%20to%20take%20some%20of%20the%20first%20night-time%20photographs%20of%20wild%20leopards%2C%20sloth%20bears%2C%20dholes%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%2076%2C%20he%20passed%20away%20in%201970%2C%20but%20the%20legacy%20he%20leaves%20behind%20is%20remarkable.%20A%20man%20ahead%20of%20his%20time%2C%20he%20advocated%20for%20a%20strong%20forest%20department%20in%20India.%20He%20believed%20they%20had%20a%20duty%20and%20responsibility%20to%20protect%20wild%20animals%20like%20the%20tiger%20and%20their%20forest%20habitats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20argue%20that%20Project%20Tiger%2C%20which%20Indira%20Gandhi%20launched%20as%20prime%20minister%20back%20in%20April%201973%2C%20is%20in%20many%20ways%20the%20legacy%20of%20Champion%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F223419%2Fpadma-shri-kailash-sankhala-project-tiger-kanha-sariska-india-unsung-hero-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20director%20of%20Project%20tiger%20and%20a%20legendary%20conservationist%2C%20once%20said%20that%20if%20tigers%20had%20been%20given%20a%20vote%2C%20the%20Corbett%20National%20Park%20would%20have%20been%20named%20after%20Champion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20understand%20what%20real%20wildlife%20photography%20feels%20like%2C%20here%E2%80%99s%20what%20Champion%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20pictures%2C%20hanging%20on%20one%E2%80%99s%20walls%20in%20subsequent%20years%2C%20bring%20back%20vividly%2C%20as%20no%20skin%20or%20head%20can%20ever%20do%2C%20what%20may%20have%20been%20the%20most%20thrilling%20moments%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20life.%20Surely%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20photographs%2C%20one%20can%20half-close%20one%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20and%20see%2C%20not%20photographs%2C%20but%20real%20scenes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRazaKazmi17%2Fstatus%2F1534373304697761792%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETwitter%2FRaza%20Kazmi%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fin.ernet.dli.2015.221331%2Fpage%2Fn91%2Fmode%2F2up%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98With%20A%20Camera%20In%20Tiger-Land%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20by%20FW%20Champion%2C%20Published%20in%201927%3B%20courtesy%20Digital%20Library%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-other-hero-walter-champion-in-jim-corbett-shadow%2Fcid%2F1794459%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20other%20hero%3A%20In%20Jim%20Corbett%E2%80%99s%20shadow%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20by%20Mahesh%20Rangarajan%2C%20Published%20on%2013%20October%202020%3B%20courtesy%20The%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frajajitigerreserve.co.in%2Fnew%2Forigin-of-rajaji-sanctuary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Origin%20of%20Rajaji%20Sanctuary%E2%