%20he%20experienced%20how%2C%20even%20in%20the%20darkest%20of%20times%2C%20humanity%20still%20survived.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amolak%20Singh%20Bhatia%20interviewed%20by%20Sahiba%20Kaur%20Chhabra%2C%20Photo%20courtesy%3A%20The%201947%20Partition%20Archive.%C2%A0%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fpartition-of-1947-1-1755179864-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-487355%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAmolak%20Singh%20Bhatia%20interviewed%20by%20Sahiba%20Kaur%20Chhabra%2C%20Photo%20courtesy%3A%20The%201947%20Partition%20Archive.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYear%201947%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENothing%20in%20the%20air%20suggested%20the%20day%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20life-changing%20one%20for%20Amolak%20Singh%20Bhatia.%20He%20woke%20up.%20Proceeded%20with%20his%20routine.%20Did%20not%20dwell%20too%20much%20on%20the%20rumours%20that%20India%20was%20going%20to%20be%20divided.%C2%A0Even%20if%20that%20happened%2C%20his%20village%2C%20Dheerkay%20Kalan%20(present-day%20Pakistan)%2C%20was%20too%20small%20to%20be%20affected%2C%20he%20believed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Sahiba%20Kaur%20Chhabra%2C%20part%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%201947%20Partition%20Archive%3C%2Fem%3E%20team%2C%20retells%20the%20story%20of%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F316761%2Fhistory-and-origin-of-tandoor-from-indus-valley-to-moti-mahal-kundal-lal-gujral%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigration%20to%20India%20during%20Partition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20shares%20how%20the%20magnanimity%20of%20the%20event%20took%20years%20to%20settle%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20truck%20came%20to%20take%20the%20family%20to%20the%20station%20from%20where%20they%20would%20go%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20my%20great-grandfather%20quickly%20scribbled%20an%20%3Cem%3Eamanat%20nama%3C%2Fem%3E%20(trust%20document)%20bequeathing%20all%20their%20assets%20to%20their%20Muslim%20neighbours%20until%20the%20time%20they%20got%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sahiba%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20be%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20was%20the%20promise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFate%20knew%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20Amolak%E2%80%99s%20memories%20of%20Partition%20are%20coloured%20with%20fear%2C%20confusion%2C%20and%20grief%2C%20there%20are%20two%20stories%20he%20always%20tells%20Sahiba%2C%20to%20underscore%20how%2C%20even%20in%20the%20darkest%20of%20times%2C%20humanity%20breathed%20hope.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESahiba%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20train%20journey%20to%20Amritsar%2C%20there%20was%20a%20rumour%20that%20the%20railway%20station%20water%20had%20been%20poisoned%20so%20that%20anyone%20who%20drank%20the%20water%20would%20die.%20A%20military%20personnel%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Muslim%2C%20who%20was%20assigned%20the%20duty%20of%20taking%20this%20cohort%20of%20people%20to%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20border%20%E2%80%94%20volunteered%20to%20drink%20the%20water%20and%20test%20it.%20%E2%80%98Even%20if%20it%20is%20poisoned%2C%20I%20will%20die.%20You%20will%20all%20be%20safe%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20told%20the%20people%20on%20the%20train.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20stories%20underscore%20an%20irony.%20While%20religion%20became%20the%20pretext%20of%20Partition%2C%20it%20also%20became%20the%20reason%20for%20hope.%20And%2C%20in%20these%20conversations%2C%20I%20found%20the%20answer%20to%20my%20question.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20scars%20ever%20heal%3F%20Does%20the%20pain%20ever%20lessen%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20lives%20on.%20In%20the%20changed%20food%20habits%20of%20the%20people%20who%20crossed%20the%20border%2C%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98we%E2%80%99ll%20be%20back%E2%80%99s%20that%20were%20never%20fulfilled%2C%20in%20the%20crinkle%20of%20their%20eyes%20every%20time%20they%20think%20of%20how%20they%20shut%20their%20home%20doors%20for%20one%20last%20time%20%E2%80%94%20knowing%20they%E2%80%99d%20never%20return.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20wound%20is%20there.%20The%20bleeding%20has%20stopped.%20But%20the%20scar%20might%20never%20fade.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20again%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20how%20you%20see%20scars.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20either%20be%20reminders%20of%20hurt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOr%20reminders%20of%20survival.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755261000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2Fbahrisons-booksellers-4-1755179130.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D487322%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%201947%2C%20India%20witnessed%20Partition.%20While%20violence%20colours%20most%20narratives%20around%20this%20historic%20event%2C%20there%20are%20also%20stories%20of%20hope%2C%20humanity%20and%20friendship%20that%20emerge.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20taking%20a%20look%20at%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F487322%2Fthe-1947-partition-archive-tells-stories-of-friendship-love-hope-independence-day%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20HC%20Denies%20Interim%20Relief%20to%20Kejriwal%2C%20Gives%20ED%20Time%20Till%20Next%20Week%20to%20Reply%20to%20Challenge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F23140650%2FScreenshot-2024-03-23-at-2.04.36.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Delhi%20high%20court%20denied%20interim%20relief%20to%20chief%20minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20financial%20crimes%20agency%20last%20week%20in%20the%20alleged%20Delhi%20liquor%20policy%20scam%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20gave%20the%20ED%20time%20till%20April%202%20to%20file%20its%20response%20to%20Kejriwal%E2%80%99s%20plea%20challenging%20his%20arrest%20as%20well%20as%20his%20application%20seeking%20interim%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20court%20is%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20that%20the%20respondent%20has%20to%20be%20granted%20an%20opportunity%20to%20file%20a%20reply%2C%20as%20an%20opportunity%20for%20effective%20representation%2C%20and%20declining%20this%20opportunity%20would%20amount%20to%20denial%20of%20fair%20hearing%20as%20well%20as%20violation%20of%20one%20of%20the%20principles%20of%20natural%20justice%20%E2%80%A6%20which%20is%20applicable%20to%20both%20the%20parties%20and%20not%20one%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F1711544457719-530817.pdf%5C%22%3EJustice%20Swarna%20Kanta%20Sharma%E2%80%99s%20order%20read%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Sharma%20also%20said%20that%20both%20Kejriwal%E2%80%99s%20petition%20challenging%20his%20arrest%20and%20his%20interim%20relief%20application%20will%20be%20decided%20on%20April%203%20and%20that%20no%20adjournment%20would%20be%20granted%20on%20that%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%2C%20who%20is%20also%20head%20of%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20ED%20on%20March%2021%20and%20is%20accused%20of%20being%20the%20%E2%80%9Ckingpin%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20liquor%20policy%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20AAP%20government%20in%20Delhi%20is%20accused%20of%20granting%20liquor%20licenses%20to%20certain%20traders%20in%20exchange%20for%20bribes%20under%20a%20now-scrapped%20liquor%20policy%20first%20implemented%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParty%20leader%20and%20Delhi%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Manish%20Sisodia%20has%20been%20jailed%20in%20the%20case%20since%20February%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP%20has%20denied%20the%20charges%20as%20being%20politically%20motivated%2C%20while%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government%20says%20the%20law%20is%20just%20taking%20its%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20said%20in%20the%20court%20that%20his%20arrest%20just%20before%20general%20elections%20violated%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Farvind-kejriwal-arrest-no-interim-relief-delhi-high-court-ed-liquor-scam-253540%5C%22%3Ewhich%20provides%20for%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20legal%20news%20site%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20ED%2C%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20S.V.%20Raju%20said%20Kejriwal%E2%80%99s%20legal%20team%20intentionally%20tried%20to%20stall%20the%20matter%20and%20provided%20the%20government%20with%20his%20400-page%20petition%20just%20yesterday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinghvi%20said%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20registry%20was%20closed%20for%20Holi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%20was%20given%20custody%20of%20Kejriwal%20until%20tomorrow%20(Thursday%2C%20March%2028).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20produced%20before%20a%20Delh